Model.ModelDescription:
In this model, clients are delayed at several delay stations each according to different probability distributions. The durations are recorded and displayed in the form of histograms.
During the animation it can be observed how the histograms are getting closer to the theoretical distributions, but even after a longer animation time there are still deviations between the exact values and the histogram values.

ModelElementText.ModelElementTextLine: Even after several thousand client arrivals or, in this case, after several thousand
random numbers generated per probability distribution under consideration, the exact
theoretical values still do not emerge. Until the histograms of the measured values
correspond perfectly to the theoretical distributions, very many client arrivals are necessary.
Therefore, even when simulating queuing models with limited numbers of client arrivals
in each case, it cannot be expected that exact values will result or that exactly the
same result values will be obtained every time the simulation is repeated.
The x-axis range in all diagrams is from 0 to 100.
The gray histogram bars on the right indicate the proportion >100.
